Hargrove Montre\u0301al Jazz\n\nTrumpeter Roy Hargrove was born in Waco, TX, in 1969. Musically inclined from a very young age, the gifted musician pursued advanced studies at the Booker T. Washington School for the Visual and Performing Arts, in Dallas. It was there that Wynton Marsalis discovered Hargrove's brilliant talents, resulting in an invitation for the young student to sit in with Marsalis's group and to rub shoulders with such jazz greats as Dizzy Gillespie and Freddie Hubbard. In 1990, he released his debut solo album, Diamond in the Rough, to world praise. Widely considered among his peers as one of the most innovative and finest trumpeters of his generation, Roy Hargrove has since released numerous acclaimed albums, including Emergence in 2009, featuring a 19-piece big band.\n\nAfter impressing us with his big band in 2010, Roy Hargrove returns with his \u201cregular\u201d quintet to unveil yet another facet of his repertoire. Of course, whatever the context, format or program, the brilliant trumpeter further burnishes his reputation for creativity and innovation with every one of his (all too rare) Festival visits. It will be a genuine privilege to experience this remarkable jazzman in the intimate confines of the Ges\u00f9, where he\u2019ll be playing for the very first time!\n\nMarc-Andr\u00e9 Sarault (Festival International de Jazz de Montr\u00e9al)\nIt\u2019s an all-too-rare visit from this excellent trumpeter.
